use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104shh1665702750613.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/shh1665702750613.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/shh1665702750613.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"shh1665702750613\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n Developing Desktop Applications \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"shh1665702750613__p_d23765e1_d23766e1_d23767e1\">By default, Uniface desktop applications are Windows applications, but it is also possible to maintain character mode applications on any supported platform.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"shh1665702750613__table_d2651e1_d2652e1_d2653e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry valign-top\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Desktop Applications</strong>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11774e1_d11775e1_d11776e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"igi1665702750681.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/igi1665702750681.html\" title=\"When developing a desktop application you follow the normal Uniface development paradigm of model, construct, compile, and test.\">Developing a Uniface Desktop Application</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11777e1_d11778e1_d11779e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxt1665702612061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxt1665702612061.html\" title=\"Forms are presentation components used in desktop applications and reports are used for printing. They are created in the same way.\">Constructing Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11780e1_d11781e1_d11782e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dig1705473594272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272.html\" title=\"Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform.\">Define a Windows Application Shell</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11783e1_d11784e1_d11785e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qjd1665702751029.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qjd1665702751029.html\" title=\"A Uniface desktop application is a traditional client/server application which can run on a local machine with access to remote functionality when needed.\">How a Desktop Application Works</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry valign-top\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Developing the User Interface</strong>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11786e1_d11787e1_d11788e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"usl1704692305727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/usl1704692305727.html\" title=\"Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms).\">Forms</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11789e1_d11790e1_d11791e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1705472567076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1705472567076.html\" title=\"An application shell is the first object that is executed when a Windows or character mode application is started. It determines how the application is initialized and the first form component that is displayed.\">Application Shells for Desktop Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11792e1_d11793e1_d11794e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zck1665702627225.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zck1665702627225.html\" title=\"Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in components running on Windows.\">Widgets for Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11795e1_d11796e1_d11797e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifp1665702614021.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifp1665702614021.html\" title=\"Labels are objects that contain static. Most labels are associated with a field, but unassociated labels can be used for any static text on the component.\">Labels in Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11798e1_d11799e1_d11800e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vfw1705577424699.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vfw1705577424699.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to define menu bar, drop-down menu, and pop-up menu objects for use in Windows applications.\">Menu Objects</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11801e1_d11802e1_d11803e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bgv1665702551096.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bgv1665702551096.html\" title=\"A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment.\">Global Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Scripting</strong>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11804e1_d11805e1_d11806e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ibf1665702751331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ibf1665702751331.html\" title=\"Triggers for preprocessing determine what happens when something new happens. Triggers for postprocessing determine what happens after an event is completed.\">Triggers for Pre- and Post-Processing</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11807e1_d11808e1_d11809e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qig1665702751409.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qig1665702751409.html\" title=\"Much report writing is data-driven—you might want to print a number of different things in different situations, depending on the data in the report. This involves using conditional ProcScript that checks what is happening in the form and directs the print process accordingly.\">Triggers for Printing</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11810e1_d11811e1_d11812e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zpq1665702751481.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zpq1665702751481.html\" title=\"The ProcScript language provides print-specific statements and functions, but there are also instructions that should be avoided in reports.\">ProcScript for Printing and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11813e1_d11814e1_d11815e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eoe1705578839705.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eoe1705578839705.html\" title=\"You control how a menu item is displayed by using the ProcScript instructions in the preDisplay trigger.\">ProcScript for Menus</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry valign-top\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Developing Reports for Printing </strong></p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11816e1_d11817e1_d11818e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ccr1704692448139.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ccr1704692448139.html\" title=\"Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing.\">Reports</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11819e1_d11820e1_d11821e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrb1665702688237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrb1665702688237.html\" title=\"Both forms and reports can be used for printing, but report components are the most appropriate choice when you need to provide specialized print control or batch processing. A report component does not allow user interaction or database I/O.\">Design Guidelines for Printing</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"shh1665702750613__li_d11822e1_d11823e1_d11824e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qyd1665702989016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyd1665702989016.html\" title=\"Uniface supports printing from form and report components, which determine the content and layout of the data to be printed.\">Printing from Uniface</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr> <tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Developing Desktop Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Developing Desktop Applications Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications. By default, Uniface desktop applications are Windows applications, but it is also possible to maintain character mode applications on any supported platform. Desktop Applications Developing a Uniface Desktop Application Constructing Forms and Reports Define a Windows Application Shell How a Desktop Application Works Developing the User Interface Forms Application Shells for Desktop Applications Widgets for Forms and Reports Labels in Forms and Reports Menu Objects Global Objects Scripting Triggers for Pre- and Post-Processing Triggers for Printing ProcScript for Printing and Reports ProcScript for Menus Developing Reports for Printing Reports Design Guidelines for Printing Printing from Uniface Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}